<p>I have a collection view and I want to animate it's cell on the tap of a button, the animation effect should be exactly as reload sections but I don't want to use      </p>  <pre><code>[self.collectionView reloadSections:[NSIndexSet indexSetWithIndex:CollectionViewSectionTypeContent]]; </code></pre>  <p>Can I acheive that using UIViewAnimation?</p>  <p>I have tried following code to animate but it's not exact same animation</p>  <pre><code>        [UIView animateWithDuration:0.5f delay:0.0 options:UIViewAnimationOptionCurveLinear  animations:^{         [cell setAlpha:1.0f];         } completion:nil]; </code></pre>